        "text": "We used to watch matches together as a kid — my dad would cheer loudly even though we had no TV! I still remember the 2015 Durand Cup final (event), we were so excited.",
        "tone": "proud",
        "sensitive": false,
        "first_seen": "2026-06-08",
        "last_seen": "2026-06-08",
        "mentions": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "mo_006",
        "text": "But I miss having someone to talk to about the game, you know? And about life. Now it's just me and the TV. It's like the stadium is empty inside sometimes.",
        "tone": "lonely",
        "sensitive": true,
        "first_seen": "2026-06-08",
        "last_seen": "2026-06-08",
        "mentions": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "mo_007",
        "text": "My dad taught me: 'Akhon bhap, porer din bhap' — today we lose, tomorrow we win. That spirit is what I try to carry in my exam prep, even though I miss talking to him now.",
        "tone": "grateful",
        "sensitive": true,
        "first_seen": "2026-06-08",
        "last_seen": "2026-06-08",
        "mentions": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "mo_008",
        "text": "The 2019 I-League final (event) — Mohun Bagan vs Kerala Blasters. I sneaked out of the library to watch on my phone, and when Mohun Bagan won, I could almost hear my dad cheering. I felt so connected to him that day, even though we were miles apart. It gave me strength to keep studying.",
        "tone": "hopeful",
        "sensitive": false,
        "first_seen": "2026-06-08",
        "last_seen": "2026-06-08",
        "mentions": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "mo_009",
        "text": "Football teaches me you can't win alone — you need a team. My dad always said, 'Ekti khel, ekti jibon' — one game, one life. Every pass, every goal, it takes trust in others. That's how I try to study too.",
        "tone": "grateful",
        "sensitive": false,
        "first_seen": "2026-06-08",
        "last_seen": "2026-06-08",
        "mentions": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "mo_010",
        "text": "My first derby was at age 10 — I held my dad's hand in a stadium full of noise like thunder. Red and maroon flags flying everywhere, the smell of food, the singing - it felt like a festival. I felt both excited and scared at the same time. I will never forget that day.",
        "tone": "proud",
        "sensitive": false,
        "first_seen": "2026-06-30",
        "last_seen": "2026-06-30",
        "mentions": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "mo_011",
        "text": "When everyone sings the same song with the same passion, it's not just a song — it's a feeling, a connection between people. It makes you feel strong, like you're with hundreds of thousands of others. That's why I love the anthems so much. Even when I'm just singing along at home, they give me energy.",
        "tone": "grateful",
        "sensitive": false,
        "first_seen": "2026-06-30",
        "last_seen": "2026-06-30",
        "mentions": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "mo_012",
        "text": "I was watching the Kolkata Derby between East Bengal and Mohun Bagan (event) with my friends, and when East Bengal scored that late winner, we all went mental! It was one of those moments you carry with you forever.",
        "tone": "proud",
        "sensitive": false,
        "first_seen": "2026-07-20",
        "last_seen": "2026-07-20",
        "mentions": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "mo_013",
        "text": "When the crowd is going wild, you just feel the energy. It's not just a game anymore—it's like a storm! That's what I love most about football.",
        "tone": "content",
        "sensitive": false,
        "first_seen": "2026-07-20",
        "last_seen": "2026-07-20",
        "mentions": 1
      }
    ],
